headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 38 points and 13 rebounds in just 29 minutes, and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Charlotte Hornets 121-82 on Friday night for their seventh straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 38 in romp, 76ers rout Hornets 121-82

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Steve Kerr still believes in his defending NBA champion Golden State Warriors' postseason chances.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, Hawks hand Warriors 10th straight road loss, 127-119

headlines.description: — Darius Garland had 24 points and nine assists, Donovan Mitchell scored 20 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers never trailed in a 117-94 victory over the Washington Wizards on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darius Garland has 24 points, Cavaliers beat Wizards 117-94

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored a season-high 49 points, Zach LaVine finished with 39 and the Chicago Bulls beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 139-131 in double overtime on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan scores 49 as Bulls beat Timberwolves in double OT

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Rookie Jabari Smith Jr. hit a 3-pointer with less than a second remaining to give the Houston Rockets a 114-112 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Friday night in the first of straight games between the teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith hits late 3-pointer, Rockets beat Pelicans 114-112

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 28 points and the Memphis Grizzlies completed the largest comeback in franchise history after trailing by 29 in the third quarter, rallying to beat the San Antonio Spurs 126-120 in overtime Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies rally from 29 down, stun Spurs 126-120 in OT

events.name: Boston Celtics at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 34 points and 12 rebounds, and the Boston Celtics withstood a late Portland rally for a 126-112 victory over the struggling Trail Blazers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 34, Celtics hold off Trail Blazers 126-112

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Maxi Kleber drilled the winning 3-pointer at the buzzer on a crosscourt pass from Kyrie Irving, who scored 38 points in the Dallas Mavericks' stunning 111-110 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxi Kleber hits 3 at buzzer, Mavericks stun Lakers 111-110
